            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EAmaziah%20learned%20the%20lesson%20of%20unquestioning%20obedience.%20He%20had%20already%20invested%20one%20hundred%20talents%20of%20silver%20to%20hire%20ungodly%20mercenary%20troops%20from%20Israel%20for%20help%20in%20the%20battle%20against%20Edom.%20Then%20the%20prophet%20instructed%20him%20to%20refuse%20any%20allies%20that%20were%20not%20on%20the%20Lord's%20side%2C%20even%20if%20they%20had%20already%20been%20paid.%20Amaziah%20faced%20a%20tough%20choice%3A%20to%20lose%20his%20investment%20and%20follow%20God%2C%20or%20keep%20his%20investment%20and%20be%20on%20his%20own.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELosing%20a%20job%2C%20money%2C%20or%20investments%20is%20never%20as%20great%20a%20loss%20as%20that%20of%20losing%20the%20presence%20of%20God.%20Paul%20admonishes%2C%20%22Don't%20copy%20the%20behavior%20and%20customs%20of%20this%20world%2C%20but%20let%20God%20transform%20you%20into%20a%20new%20person%20by%20changing%20the%20way%20you%20think.%20Then%20you%20will%20know%20what%20God%20wants%20you%20to%20do%2C%20and%20you%20will%20know%20how%20good%20and%20pleasing%20and%20perfect%20his%20will%20really%20is%22%20(Romans%2012%3A2).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELife%20is%20full%20of%20tough%20decisions%20in%20which%20you%20must%20choose%20between%20God's%20will%20and%20apparent%20wealth%2C%20fame%2C%20or%20strength.%20In%20actuality%2C%20the%20Lord%20can%20give%20you%20much%20more%20than%20anything%20you%20sacrifice%20for%20Him%20(2%20Chronicles%2025%3A10).%20Never%20value%20any%20worldly%20thing%20more%20than%20you%20value%20being%20in%20the%20peace%20and%20rest%20of%20God.%20Choose%20God's%20way%2C%20for%20as%20Romans%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E8%3A31%20promises%2C%20if%20God%20is%20for%20you%2C%20who%20can%20be%20against%20you%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.24:1-25:28",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2024%3A1-25%3A28%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJoash%20Repairs%20the%20Temple%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EJoash%20was%20seven%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20forty%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Zibiah%20from%20Beersheba.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EJoash%20did%20what%20was%20pleasing%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%20throughout%20the%20lifetime%20of%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoiada%20chose%20two%20wives%20for%20Joash%2C%20and%20he%20had%20sons%20and%20daughters.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20one%20point%20Joash%20decided%20to%20repair%20and%20restore%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20summoned%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%20and%20gave%20them%20these%20instructions%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BGo%20to%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah%20and%20collect%20the%20required%20annual%20offerings%2C%20so%20that%20we%20can%20repair%20the%20Temple%20of%20your%20God.%20Do%20not%20delay!%26%23x201D%3B%20But%20the%20Levites%20did%20not%20act%20immediately.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20king%20called%20for%20Jehoiada%20the%20high%20priest%20and%20asked%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20haven%26%23x2019%3Bt%20you%20demanded%20that%20the%20Levites%20go%20out%20and%20collect%20the%20Temple%20taxes%20from%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah%20and%20from%20Jerusalem%3F%20Moses%2C%20the%20servant%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20levied%20this%20tax%20on%20the%20community%20of%20Israel%20in%20order%20to%20maintain%20the%20Tabernacle%20of%20the%20Covenant.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E24%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ETent%20of%20the%20Testimony.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EOver%20the%20years%20the%20followers%20of%20wicked%20Athaliah%20had%20broken%20into%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%2C%20and%20they%20had%20used%20all%20the%20dedicated%20things%20from%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20worship%20the%20images%20of%20Baal.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20now%20the%20king%20ordered%20a%20chest%20to%20be%20made%20and%20set%20outside%20the%20gate%20leading%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20a%20proclamation%20was%20sent%20throughout%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%2C%20telling%20the%20people%20to%20bring%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20tax%20that%20Moses%2C%20the%20servant%20of%20God%2C%20had%20required%20of%20the%20Israelites%20in%20the%20wilderness.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20pleased%20all%20the%20leaders%20and%20the%20people%2C%20and%20they%20gladly%20brought%20their%20money%20and%20filled%20the%20chest%20with%20it.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EWhenever%20the%20chest%20became%20full%2C%20the%20Levites%20would%20carry%20it%20to%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20officials.%20Then%20the%20court%20secretary%20and%20an%20officer%20of%20the%20high%20priest%20would%20come%20and%20empty%20the%20chest%20and%20take%20it%20back%20to%20the%20Temple%20again.%20This%20went%20on%20day%20after%20day%2C%20and%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20money%20was%20collected.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20and%20Jehoiada%20gave%20the%20money%20to%20the%20construction%20supervisors%2C%20who%20hired%20masons%20and%20carpenters%20to%20restore%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20They%20also%20hired%20metalworkers%2C%20who%20made%20articles%20of%20iron%20and%20bronze%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20men%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20renovation%20worked%20hard%20and%20made%20steady%20progress.%20They%20restored%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20according%20to%20its%20original%20design%20and%20strengthened%20it.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20all%20the%20repairs%20were%20finished%2C%20they%20brought%20the%20remaining%20money%20to%20the%20king%20and%20Jehoiada.%20It%20was%20used%20to%20make%20various%20articles%20for%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2014%3Barticles%20for%20worship%20services%20and%20for%20burnt%20offerings%2C%20including%20ladles%20and%20other%20articles%20made%20of%20gold%20and%20silver.%20And%20the%20burnt%20offerings%20were%20sacrificed%20continually%20in%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20during%20the%20lifetime%20of%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoiada%20lived%20to%20a%20very%20old%20age%2C%20finally%20dying%20at%20130.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20was%20buried%20among%20the%20kings%20in%20the%20City%20of%20David%2C%20because%20he%20had%20done%20so%20much%20good%20in%20Israel%20for%20God%20and%20his%20Temple.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoiada%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Reforms%20Reversed%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20after%20Jehoiada%26%23x2019%3Bs%20death%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20Judah%20came%20and%20bowed%20before%20King%20Joash%20and%20persuaded%20him%20to%20listen%20to%20their%20advice.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20decided%20to%20abandon%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors%2C%20and%20they%20worshiped%20Asherah%20poles%20and%20idols%20instead!%20Because%20of%20this%20sin%2C%20divine%20anger%20fell%20on%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EYet%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sent%20prophets%20to%20bring%20them%20back%20to%20him.%20The%20prophets%20warned%20them%2C%20but%20still%20the%20people%20would%20not%20listen.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20Spirit%20of%20God%20came%20upon%20Zechariah%20son%20of%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest.%20He%20stood%20before%20the%20people%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20God%20says%3A%20Why%20do%20you%20disobey%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20commands%20and%20keep%20yourselves%20from%20prospering%3F%20You%20have%20abandoned%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20and%20now%20he%20has%20abandoned%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20leaders%20plotted%20to%20kill%20Zechariah%2C%20and%20King%20Joash%20ordered%20that%20they%20stone%20him%20to%20death%20in%20the%20courtyard%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThat%20was%20how%20King%20Joash%20repaid%20Jehoiada%20for%20his%20loyalty%26%23x2014%3Bby%20killing%20his%20son.%20Zechariah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20last%20words%20as%20he%20died%20were%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20see%20what%20they%20are%20doing%20and%20avenge%20my%20death!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20End%20of%20Joash%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Reign%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20spring%20of%20the%20year%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E24%3A23%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EAt%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20first%20day%20of%20the%20year%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20occurred%20in%20March%20or%20April.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20Aramean%20army%20marched%20against%20Joash.%20They%20invaded%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%20and%20killed%20all%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20nation.%20Then%20they%20sent%20all%20the%20plunder%20back%20to%20their%20king%20in%20Damascus.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EAlthough%20the%20Arameans%20attacked%20with%20only%20a%20small%20army%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20helped%20them%20conquer%20the%20much%20larger%20army%20of%20Judah.%20The%20people%20of%20Judah%20had%20abandoned%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors%2C%20so%20judgment%20was%20carried%20out%20against%20Joash.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Arameans%20withdrew%2C%20leaving%20Joash%20severely%20wounded.%20But%20his%20own%20officials%20plotted%20to%20kill%20him%20for%20murdering%20the%20son%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E24%3A25%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20and%20Latin%20Vulgate%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Esons.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest.%20They%20assassinated%20him%20as%20he%20lay%20in%20bed.%20Then%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20the%20City%20of%20David%2C%20but%20not%20in%20the%20royal%20cemetery.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20assassins%20were%20Jozacar%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E24%3A26a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2012%3A21%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EZabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20son%20of%20an%20Ammonite%20woman%20named%20Shimeath%2C%20and%20Jehozabad%2C%20the%20son%20of%20a%20Moabite%20woman%20named%20Shomer.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E24%3A26b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2012%3A21%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EShimrith%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Shomer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_24_27%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20account%20of%20the%20sons%20of%20Joash%2C%20the%20prophecies%20about%20him%2C%20and%20the%20record%20of%20his%20restoration%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20are%20written%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Commentary%20on%20the%20Book%20of%20the%20Kings.%3C%2Fem%3E%20His%20son%20Amaziah%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAmaziah%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20was%20twenty-five%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20twenty-nine%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Jehoaddin%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E25%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2014%3A2%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EJehoaddan%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoaddin.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20from%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20did%20what%20was%20pleasing%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20but%20not%20wholeheartedly.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Amaziah%20was%20well%20established%20as%20king%2C%20he%20executed%20the%20officials%20who%20had%20assassinated%20his%20father.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHowever%2C%20he%20did%20not%20kill%20the%20children%20of%20the%20assassins%2C%20for%20he%20obeyed%20the%20command%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20written%20by%20Moses%20in%20the%20Book%20of%20the%20Law%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BParents%20must%20not%20be%20put%20to%20death%20for%20the%20sins%20of%20their%20children%2C%20nor%20children%20for%20the%20sins%20of%20their%20parents.%20Those%20deserving%20to%20die%20must%20be%20put%20to%20death%20for%20their%20own%20crimes.%26%23x201D%3B%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E25%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Deut%2024%3A16.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Amaziah%20organized%20the%20army%2C%20assigning%20generals%20and%20captains%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E25%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ecommanders%20of%20thousands%20and%20commanders%20of%20hundreds.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20all%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin.%20He%20took%20a%20census%20and%20found%20that%20he%20had%20an%20army%20of%20300%2C000%20select%20troops%2C%20twenty%20years%20old%20and%20older%2C%20all%20trained%20in%20the%20use%20of%20spear%20and%20shield.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20also%20paid%20about%207%2C500%20pounds%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E25%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E100%26%23xA0%3Btalents%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B3%2C400%20kilograms%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20silver%20to%20hire%20100%2C000%20experienced%20fighting%20men%20from%20Israel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20a%20man%20of%20God%20came%20to%20him%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYour%20Majesty%2C%20do%20not%20hire%20troops%20from%20Israel%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20not%20with%20Israel.%20He%20will%20not%20help%20those%20people%20of%20Ephraim!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EIf%20you%20let%20them%20go%20with%20your%20troops%20into%20battle%2C%20you%20will%20be%20defeated%20by%20the%20enemy%20no%20matter%20how%20well%20you%20fight.%20God%20will%20overthrow%20you%2C%20for%20he%20has%20the%20power%20to%20help%20you%20or%20to%20trip%20you%20up.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EAmaziah%20asked%20the%20man%20of%20God%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBut%20what%20about%20all%20that%20silver%20I%20paid%20to%20hire%20the%20army%20of%20Israel%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThe%20man%20of%20God%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20able%20to%20give%20you%20much%20more%20than%20this!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Amaziah%20discharged%20the%20hired%20troops%20and%20sent%20them%20back%20to%20Ephraim.%20This%20made%20them%20very%20angry%20with%20Judah%2C%20and%20they%20returned%20home%20in%20a%20great%20rage.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Amaziah%20summoned%20his%20courage%20and%20led%20his%20army%20to%20the%20Valley%20of%20Salt%2C%20where%20they%20killed%2010%2C000%20Edomite%20troops%20from%20Seir.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20captured%20another%2010%2C000%20and%20took%20them%20to%20the%20top%20of%20a%20cliff%20and%20threw%20them%20off%2C%20dashing%20them%20to%20pieces%20on%20the%20rocks%20below.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20hired%20troops%20that%20Amaziah%20had%20sent%20home%20raided%20several%20of%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah%20between%20Samaria%20and%20Beth-horon.%20They%20killed%203%2C000%20people%20and%20carried%20off%20great%20quantities%20of%20plunder.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20King%20Amaziah%20returned%20from%20slaughtering%20the%20Edomites%2C%20he%20brought%20with%20him%20idols%20taken%20from%20the%20people%20of%20Seir.%20He%20set%20them%20up%20as%20his%20own%20gods%2C%20bowed%20down%20in%20front%20of%20them%2C%20and%20offered%20sacrifices%20to%20them!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_25_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20made%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20very%20angry%2C%2